(25. SkewDB: an open database of GC and other microbial skews) Tj
T*
(Source: Bert Hubert's writings | Published: Mon, 30 Aug 2021 14:19:18 +0200) Tj
T*
(Link:) Tj
T*
(https://berthub.eu/articles/posts/skewdb-an-open-database-of-gc-and-other-microbial-skews/) Tj
T*
(Hello and welcome to this introduction of the SkewDB. This open \(downloadable\) database) Tj
T*
(contains details of GC skew, plus a dozen other skews, for all 28,000 bacterial chromosomes) Tj
T*
(available through the NCBI genomes service. The database is created using the open source) Tj
T*
(Antonie DNA software. There is also an online viewer that includes graphs. GC skew is the) Tj
T*
(phenomenon where almost all circular chromosomes tend to have near equal amounts of G and C) Tj
T*
(nucleotides, per strand, but where the leading replication strand contains an excess of G, and) Tj
T*
(the lagging replication strand has an excess of C nucleotides.) Tj
T*
() Tj
